Colonial Office Sierra Leone
28th December 1870

Sir,

I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of your letter No 24 of the 27th instant respecting the detention of the of the American Schooner "Kettle" by the Collector of Customs, in consequence of a violation of the order in Council of 13th February 1849.

Having laid the same before His Excellency The Governor-In-Chief I am disceted to inform you that His Excellency does not think its necessary to direct any proceedin in the matter, and the Collector has therefore been instructed to liberate the vessel, on pay went of any expenses which have been incurred.

I have the honor to be
Sir
Your Most Obdt Servant
J.J. Kendall
Colonial Secretary

J.B. Upton Esquire
U.S. Commercial Agent
